text.section:
Unless denied a license pursuant to § 10-410 of this subtitle, a person that is not a resident of the State may obtain a nonresident license to act as a public adjuster if:
the person currently is licensed as a resident public adjuster and in good standing in the person's home state;
the person files an application on the form that the Commissioner provides;
the person has paid the applicable fee pursuant to § 2-112 of this article; and
the person's home state awards nonresident public adjuster licenses to residents of this State on the same basis.
